Cinchona ledgeriana

    Authority   Moens
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Rubiales:Rubiaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4564

   Notes
   SOURCES (C. ledgeriana Moens ex Tremen)
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 452-458 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, DRA, FER, PH, LIMITS]
   Kernick M 1961 pp 219
   Nair P 1980 pp 261-264 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, FER, DRA, USE]
   KILLING T
   Tolerant to below 7Â°C.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Fastgrowing perennial evergreen tree. Trees are uprooted and harvested
   after 8-12 years, fruits ripen in about 240 days.
   COMMON NAMES
   Yellow quinine.
   FURTHER INF
   Yellow quinine can be grown in the tropics at altitudes from 1000-2000
   m. The tree can grow 6-16 m in height. Mentioned as a useful
   agroforestry species. The tree need protection from high winds.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
